  "text": "Cl n satisfies the property (*) at this moment since the generators in the definition of H Cl n (Definition 2.15) do not directly satisfy the relation (3.1). We will replace those symbols x i in H Cl n by some other elements and then show that those new generators satisfy the property (*) in Section 4. We hope this more general setting can cover some other interesting examples such as the Hecke-Clifford algebra for other classical types defined in [CITATION_1] .",
